Liga seasons|2016-17]]\n[[Category:2016\u201317 in European ice hockey leagues]]\n[[Category:2016\u201317 in German ice hockey]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sports season\n| title = 2016\u201317 DEL season\n| league = [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]]\n| sport = [[Ice hockey]]\n| logo = \n| duration = 16 September 2016\u201321 April 2017\n| no_of_teams = [[#Teams|14]]\n| no_of_games = 364\n| attendance = \n| season = Regular season\n| season_champs = [[EHC Red Bull M\u00fcnchen|EHC M\u00fcnchen]]\n| MVP = [[Patrick Reimer]]\n| top_scorer = [[Patrick Reimer]]<br>(54 points)\n| finals = Finals\n| finals_champ = [[EHC Red Bull M\u00fcnchen|EHC M\u00fcnchen]]\n| finals_runner-up = [[EHC Wolfsburg]]\n| finals_MVP = [[Yannic Seidenberg]]\n| seasonslist = Deutsche Eishockey Liga#DEL seasons\n| seasonslistnames = DEL\n| prevseason_link = 2015\u201316 DEL season\n| prevseason_year = 2015\u201316\n| nextseason_link = 2017\u201318 DEL season\n| nextseason_year = 2017\u201318\n}}\nThe '''2016\u201317 Deutsche Eishockey Liga season''' was the 23rd season since the founding of the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]].\n\n[[Hamburg Freezers]] did not play this season due to financial reasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/bid-to-save-hamburg-freezers-del-ice-hockey-team-comes-up-short/a-19281624|title=Bid to save Hamburg Freezers DEL ice hockey team comes up short|publisher=Deutsche Welle|language=German|date=25 May 2016|accessdate=26 May 2016}}</ref> [[Fischtown Pinguins]] were given the license to play in the DEL.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.del.org/de/news/2016/06/del-lizenz-20160701/page/4922--30-4889--4889.html|title=Bremerhaven erh\u00e4lt 14. DEL-Lizenz f\u00fcr Saison 2016/17|publisher=del.org|language=German|date=1 July 2016|accessdate=1 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816060940/http://www.del.org/de/news/2016/06/del-lizenz-20160701/page/4922--30-4889--4889.html|archive-date=16 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nMunich won their second consecutive title by defeating Wolfsburg in five games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telekomeishockey.de/news/muenchen-ist-meister-4-0-gegen-wolfsburg-7-titel-fuer-don-jackson/6965|title=M\u00fcnchen ist Meister! 4:0 gegen Wolfsburg - 7. Titel f\u00fcr Don Jackson|date=17 April 2017|work=telekomeishockey.de}}</ref>\n\n==Teams==\n{{ Location map+\n | Germany\n | width=300\n | float=right\n | caption= Teams of the 2016\u201317 DEL season\n | places=\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=<small>[[Augsburger Panther]]</small>\n | position=left\n | lat_deg=48| lat_min=22 |lat_sec=40\n | lon_deg=10| lon_min=54 |lon_sec=0\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[Eisb\u00e4ren Berlin]]\n | position=bottom\n | lat_deg=52 | lat_min=27 |lat_sec=26\n | lon_deg=13 | lon_min=34 |lon_sec=05\n | region=DE-BE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[Fischtown Pinguins]]\n | position=bottom\n | lat_deg=53 | lat_min=32 |lat_sec=00\n | lon_deg=8  | lon_min=35 |lon_sec=00\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[D\u00fcsseldorfer EG|DEG]]\n | position=right\n | lat_deg=51 | lat_min=13 |lat_sec=37\n | lon_deg=6 | lon_min=48 |lon_sec=47\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[ERC Ingolstadt]]\n | position=left\n | lat_deg=48 | lat_min=46 |lat_sec=37\n | lon_deg=11 | lon_min=26 |lon_sec=47\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[Iserlohn Roosters]]\n | position=right\n | lat_deg=51 | lat_min=23 |lat_sec=37\n | lon_deg=7 | lon_min=40 |lon_sec=47\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[K\u00f6lner Haie]]\n | position=bottom\n | lat_deg=50 | lat_min=57 |lat_sec=26\n | lon_deg=6 | lon_min=57 |lon_sec=5\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[Krefeld Pinguine]]\n | position=top\n | lat_deg=51 | lat_min=19 |lat_sec=40\n | lon_deg=6 | lon_min=33 |lon_sec=55\n | region=DE\n }}\n {{ Location map~\n | Germany\n | label=[[Adler Mannheim]]\n | position=top\n | lat_deg=49 | l